# Styling Conventions

## Formatting
- Prettier is the single source of truth for formatting.
- Do not add ESLint rules that conflict with Prettier.
- Run `pnpm format` to fix formatting issues.

## UI Component System
- Use **shadcn/ui** components as the base layer for all UI elements.
- Never create custom equivalents of existing shadcn components (Card, Button, Input, Badge, Progress, Separator, Label, etc.).
- Install new shadcn components with `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>`.
- shadcn components live in `src/components/ui/` and should not be modified unless extending a variant.

## Styling with Tailwind CSS
- Use **Tailwind CSS utility classes** for all styling — do not create custom CSS files.
- The only CSS file is `src/index.css`, which contains Tailwind directives and shadcn CSS variables.
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging (never string concatenation).
- Prefer shadcn design tokens (CSS variables like `--primary`, `--destructive`, `--muted`) over hardcoded color values.
- Use semantic Tailwind classes for status colors with dark mode variants:
  - Safe: `text-emerald-700 bg-emerald-50 border-emerald-200 dark:text-emerald-300 dark:bg-emerald-950 dark:border-emerald-800`
  - Warning: `text-amber-700 bg-amber-50 border-amber-200 dark:text-amber-300 dark:bg-amber-950 dark:border-amber-800`
  - Danger: `text-red-700 bg-red-50 border-red-200 dark:text-red-300 dark:bg-red-950 dark:border-red-800`
  - Info: `text-blue-700 bg-blue-50 border-blue-200 dark:text-blue-300 dark:bg-blue-950 dark:border-blue-800`

## Dark Mode
- Dark mode uses the `dark` class on `<html>`, toggled via `useTheme()` hook from `@/hooks/useTheme`.
- The `ThemeToggle` component cycles through light / dark / system modes, persisted in `localStorage`.
- Always add `dark:` variants when using hardcoded Tailwind color utilities (e.g., `bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-950`).
- shadcn design tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`, etc.) adapt automatically — prefer these over hardcoded colors when possible.

## Component Composition
- Follow shadcn's composition pattern: `Card` > `CardHeader` > `CardTitle` > `CardContent`.
- Use `Badge` for status indicators instead of colored dots or custom status elements.
- Use `Button` variants (`default`, `outline`, `destructive`, `secondary`, `ghost`) instead of custom button classes.
- Use `Input` + `Label` for form fields.
- Use `Separator` for visual dividers.
- Use `Progress` for progress bars.
- Use Lucide icons (`lucide-react`) for iconography — do not use emoji in headings.

## Responsive Design
- Use mobile-first responsive design with Tailwind breakpoint prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`).
- Use `max-w-6xl mx-auto` for content containment.
- Use CSS Grid (`grid`) and Flexbox (`flex`) via Tailwind for layouts.

## Import Aliases
- Use the `@/` path alias for imports from `src/` (e.g., `@/components/ui/card`, `@/lib/utils`).

## Code Comments
- Do not add comments that narrate what the code does.
- Only add comments for non-obvious intent, trade-offs, or constraints.
- Use JSDoc for public utility function documentation.
